parameters:
Queen Caron: You, who are a defeated soldier who fled from
Tarasa, are originally someone who is not even worthy of
speaking to me.

Queen Caron: However, I have heard that you have an
interesting gift. If it pleases me, I may consider sparing
your life.

Mage Eratoma: I can create dragons, mythical creatures that
once existed and soared through the skies in ancient times!

Mage Eratoma: King Tarasa lacks the determination to control
monsters, which is why I have come to serve under a powerful
ruler with a broad mind.

Mage Eratoma: If I can mass-produce dragons, we can conquer
Tarasa and the like overnight.

Queen Caron: I have one question, are your parents alive and
well in Tarasa?

Mage Eratoma: Yes, I have heard that both my parents and
other members of my clan are safe and sound.

Queen Caron: Even so, do you approve of using dragons to
conquer Tarasa?

Mage Eratoma: Compared to my research on dragons, this is a
trivial matter. Our magical power is high, making us
excellent material!

Queen Caron: Kukuku, ahahahaha! I like you, I'll keep you as
my pet for now.
Mage Eratoma: May I make a request?

Queen Caron: You're quite greedy, aren't you? Depending on
your answer, your head might roll on the ground, you know?

Mage Eratoma: I would like to have a large number of
corpses! Since the corpses of both countries are floating in
the sea, it should be easy to procure.
Mage Eratoma: Dragons cannot do without corpses...

Eratoma, who was recognized by Queen Caron, devoted himself
to the production of dragons, mobilizing all the members of
the dark faction. It was a relentless endeavor that
continued day and night, as if their lives were being
sacrificed.

After just a few months of contact with Caron, the dragons
were completed. However, these dragons were created solely
as a proof and were not satisfactory for Eratoma.

However, in an environment where he had the freedom to use
personnel, funds, and resources, Eratoma was confident that
he could create the perfect dragon he desired. He believed
this in the dimly lit room.
